==Esperanto==
===Etymology===
From negative pronouns of English ([[never]], [[none]]), Dutch (''[[niemand]]''), French (''[[ne personne]]''), German (''[[nie]]''), Italian (''[[nessuno]]''), Polish (''[[nikt]]''), Portuguese (''[[nenhum]]''), Russian ([[никто]]), and Spanish (''[[ninguno]]'')

===Affix===
[[Category:Esperanto prefixes]]
'''neni-'''
# no-. (Negative/relative [[:Category:Esperanto correlatives|correlative]] prefix.)
===Derived terms===
* ''[[neniu]]'': '''no''' individual, [[nobody]]
* ''[[nenio]]'': '''no''' object, [[nothing]]
* ''[[nenia]]'': '''no''' kind of
* ''[[nenies]]'': belonging to '''no''' one, [[nobody's]]
* ''[[neniel]]'': '''no''' manner/degree
* ''[[nenie]]'': '''no''' place, [[nowhere]]
* ''[[neniam]]'': '''no''' time, [[never]]
* ''[[neniom]]'': '''no''' quantity, [[none]] of
* ''[[nenial]]'': '''no''' reason

